<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-45-0137 </DOCNO><TEXT>Italy's Green Party (Lista Verde) does not consider itself a politicalparty but it is changing the environmental consciousness of the nation.There are new eight popular television shows covering environmental problemsand a national weekly newspaper devotes a regular column to ecology.Environmental associations, including the Environmental League, havebeen started in the 1980s. The Greens have also succeeded in haltingItaly's nuclear power programme. In a national referendum held in 1987almost 80% of the voters agreed with the Greens' views. No fewer than14 more popular referenda are planned throughout Italy on environmentalissues.</TEXT></DOC>